In conclusion, the repository provides a comprehensive analysis of hand gesture recognition models, highlighting the strengths and weaknesses of both the 
CNN-based and ensembled-based approaches. This comparative study contributes to the ongoing research in the field of computer vision and gesture recognition, 
with potential applications in sign language interpretation, 
gaming devices, and other human-computer interaction systems.
